{
  "mainWorkflow": {
    "name": "LoanApprovalProcess",
    "description": "Migrated from BPEL process LoanApprovalProcess",
    "version": 1,
    "inputParameters": [
      "clientEndpoint",
      "creditServiceEndpoint",
      "riskServiceEndpoint",
      "loanRequest",
      "loanResponse",
      "creditScore",
      "riskResult",
      "faultDetail"
    ],
    "tasks": [
      {
        "name": "wait_approveLoan",
        "taskReferenceName": "ReceiveLoanRequest",
        "type": "WAIT",
        "inputParameters": {
          "partnerLink": "client",
          "operation": "approveLoan",
          "variable": "loanRequest",
          "createInstance": "yes"
        }
      },
      {
        "name": "human_ManagerReview",
        "taskReferenceName": "ManagerReview",
        "type": "HUMAN",
        "inputParameters": {
          "staffQuery": "role:LoanManager",
          "potentialOwners": "cn=managers,ou=groups",
          "priority": "3",
          "escalationTarget": null,
          "durationExpression": null
        }
      },
      {
        "name": "fork_ParallelChecks",
        "taskReferenceName": "ParallelChecks",
        "type": "FORK_JOIN",
        "forkTasks": [
          [
            {
              "name": "creditService_checkCredit",
              "taskReferenceName": "CheckCredit",
              "type": "SIMPLE",
              "inputParameters": {
                "partnerLink": "creditService",
                "operation": "checkCredit",
                "inputVariable": "loanRequest",
                "outputVariable": "creditScore"
              }
            }
          ],
          [
            {
              "name": "riskService_assessRisk",
              "taskReferenceName": "AssessRisk",
              "type": "SIMPLE",
              "inputParameters": {
                "partnerLink": "riskService",
                "operation": "assessRisk",
                "inputVariable": "loanRequest",
                "outputVariable": "riskResult"
              }
            }
          ]
        ]
      },
      {
        "name": "join_ParallelChecks",
        "taskReferenceName": "join_ParallelChecks",
        "type": "JOIN",
        "joinOn": [
          "CheckCredit",
          "AssessRisk"
        ]
      },
      {
        "name": "switch_CreditDecision",
        "taskReferenceName": "CreditDecision",
        "type": "SWITCH",
        "evaluatorType": "javascript",
        "expression": "function execute() {\n  if ($.creditScore.score > 650 && $.riskResult.level === 'LOW') return \"branch_0__creditScore_score___650_and__riskResult\";\n  if ($.creditScore.score > 500) return \"branch_1__creditScore_score___500\";\n  return \"default\";\n}",
        "decisionCases": {
          "branch_0__creditScore_score___650_and__riskResult": [
            {
              "name": "set_SetApproved",
              "taskReferenceName": "SetApproved",
              "type": "SET_VARIABLE",
              "inputParameters": {
                "copy_0_from": {},
                "copy_0_to": {
                  "variable": "loanResponse",
                  "part": "status"
                }
              }
            }
          ],
          "branch_1__creditScore_score___500": [
            {
              "name": "set_SetReview",
              "taskReferenceName": "SetReview",
              "type": "SET_VARIABLE",
              "inputParameters": {
                "copy_0_from": {},
                "copy_0_to": {
                  "variable": "loanResponse",
                  "part": "status"
                }
              }
            }
          ]
        },
        "defaultCase": [
          {
            "name": "set_SetDenied",
            "taskReferenceName": "SetDenied",
            "type": "SET_VARIABLE",
            "inputParameters": {
              "copy_0_from": {},
              "copy_0_to": {
                "variable": "loanResponse",
                "part": "status"
              }
            }
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "name": "sub_NotificationScope",
        "taskReferenceName": "NotificationScope",
        "type": "SUB_WORKFLOW",
        "subWorkflowParam": {
          "name": "sub_NotificationScope",
          "version": 1
        }
      },
      {
        "name": "wait_timer",
        "taskReferenceName": "WaitForDocument",
        "type": "WAIT",
        "inputParameters": {
          "duration": "'PT24H'",
          "waitType": "for"
        }
      },
      {
        "name": "reply_approveLoan",
        "taskReferenceName": "ReplyToClient",
        "type": "SIMPLE",
        "inputParameters": {
          "partnerLink": "client",
          "operation": "approveLoan",
          "variable": "loanResponse",
          "faultName": null
        }
      }
    ],
    "failureWorkflow": "fault_handler_LoanApprovalProcess",
    "outputParameters": {
      "processName": "LoanApprovalProcess",
      "targetNamespace": "http://example.com/loan"
    },
    "timeoutPolicy": "ALERT_ONLY",
    "timeoutSeconds": 0
  },
  "subWorkflows": [
    {
      "name": "sub_NotificationScope",
      "tasks": [
        {
          "name": "client_notify",
          "taskReferenceName": "SendNotification",
          "type": "SIMPLE",
          "inputParameters": {
            "partnerLink": "client",
            "operation": "notify",
            "inputVariable": "loanResponse",
            "outputVariable": null
          }
        }
      ],
      "failureWorkflow": "compensate_NotificationScope"
    }
  ],
  "compensationFlows": [
    {
      "name": "compensate_LoanApprovalProcess",
      "description": "Compensation workflow for LoanApprovalProcess",
      "version": 1,
      "tasks": [
        {
          "name": "creditService_rollback",
          "taskReferenceName": "RollbackCredit",
          "type": "SIMPLE",
          "inputParameters": {
            "partnerLink": "creditService",
            "operation": "rollback",
            "inputVariable": "creditScore",
            "outputVariable": null
          }
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "name": "compensate_NotificationScope",
      "tasks": [
        {
          "name": "client_cancelNotification",
          "taskReferenceName": "CancelNotification",
          "type": "SIMPLE",
          "inputParameters": {
            "partnerLink": "client",
            "operation": "cancelNotification",
            "inputVariable": "loanResponse",
            "outputVariable": null
          }
        }
      ]
    }
  ],
  "faultHandlerFlows": [
    {
      "name": "fault_handler_LoanApprovalProcess",
      "description": "Auto-generated fault handler for LoanApprovalProcess",
      "version": 1,
      "tasks": [
        {
          "name": "route_fault",
          "taskReferenceName": "route_fault",
          "type": "SWITCH",
          "evaluatorType": "javascript",
          "expression": "$.workflow.input.error.workflowType",
          "decisionCases": {
            "CreditCheckFault": [
              {
                "name": "set_SetRejectionReason",
                "taskReferenceName": "SetRejectionReason",
                "type": "SET_VARIABLE",
                "inputParameters": {
                  "copy_0_from": {},
                  "copy_0_to": {
                    "variable": "loanResponse",
                    "part": "status"
                  }
                }
              },
              {
                "name": "reply_approveLoan",
                "taskReferenceName": "ReplyWithFault",
                "type": "SIMPLE",
                "inputParameters": {
                  "partnerLink": "client",
                  "operation": "approveLoan",
                  "variable": "loanResponse",
                  "faultName": "tns:LoanDeniedFault"
                }
              }
            ]
          },
          "defaultCase": [
            {
              "name": "terminate_tns_UnexpectedFault",
              "taskReferenceName": "RethrowGeneric",
              "type": "TERMINATE",
              "inputParameters": {
                "terminationStatus": "FAILED",
                "workflowOutput": {
                  "faultName": "tns:UnexpectedFault",
                  "faultVariable": null
                }
              }
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    }
  ],
  "warnings": [
    "[ReceiveLoanRequest] <receive> 'ReceiveLoanRequest' uses ESB push pattern \u2014 BPEL waited for an inbound message on partnerLink 'client'. In Conductor this WAIT task must be completed by an external callback: POST /api/tasks/{taskId}/ack with the payload. Wire your ESB/MQ consumer or API gateway to call that endpoint.",
    "[CheckCredit] <invoke> 'CheckCredit' \u2192 SIMPLE task (worker stub). If partnerLink 'creditService' was a SOAP/WSDL service or SCA Java component, implement a Conductor worker: register task type 'creditService_checkCredit', deploy a worker that polls GET /api/tasks/poll/..., executes the call, and posts results back. SOAP callers must handle WS envelope and security in the worker.",
    "[AssessRisk] <invoke> 'AssessRisk' \u2192 SIMPLE task (worker stub). If partnerLink 'riskService' was a SOAP/WSDL service or SCA Java component, implement a Conductor worker: register task type 'riskService_assessRisk', deploy a worker that polls GET /api/tasks/poll/..., executes the call, and posts results back. SOAP callers must handle WS envelope and security in the worker.",
    "[SendNotification] <invoke> 'SendNotification' \u2192 SIMPLE task (worker stub). If partnerLink 'client' was a SOAP/WSDL service or SCA Java component, implement a Conductor worker: register task type 'client_notify', deploy a worker that polls GET /api/tasks/poll/..., executes the call, and posts results back. SOAP callers must handle WS envelope and security in the worker.",
    "Correlation set 'loanCorrelation' (properties: t, n, s, :, l, o, a, n, I, d) is not mapped. In BPEL this routed async callbacks back to the correct process instance. In Conductor, use the workflow ID as your correlation key: pass it in every outbound HTTP call header (e.g. X-Correlation-Id: ${workflow.workflowId}) and have callers include it when posting task callbacks."
  ],
  "workflowCount": 5
}